and they may not have been as ape like as
we've previously thought with

00:36:07.210 --> 00:36:12.610
australopithecus. When we look at the
earliest Homo, we may see at least some

00:36:12.610 --> 00:36:15.590
that may have even more apey limb
proportions than we see in

00:36:15.590 --> 00:36:20.420
australopithecus. We see that the
combination of features of having larger

00:36:20.420 --> 00:36:25.310
lower limb joints, of having larger limb
joints, longer lower limbs don't

00:36:25.310 --> 00:36:29.550
necessarily co-vary. Limbs were already
long, hip joints may have been gotten big

00:36:29.550 --> 00:36:33.110
at the beginning of Homo, it's hard to
say. Body form may have evolved

00:36:33.110 --> 00:36:37.440
differently in different species and/or at
different times. But we no longer have

00:36:37.440 --> 00:36:42.260
this idea of one change associated with
the origin of the genus. And these well

00:36:42.260 --> 00:36:46.010
adapted features that we see here that
make this complex, that make Homo erectus

00:36:46.010 --> 00:36:49.910
great that do things like hunting and tool
using and everything later, may be

00:36:49.910 --> 00:36:53.670
something that weren't associated with the
origin of the genus but came in much

00:36:53.670 --> 00:36:58.450
later. So in fact, if we compare
australopithecus to earliest Homo, this

00:36:58.450 --> 00:37:02.670
might be a more reasonable picture to have
in our mind. Animals that weren't really

00:37:02.670 --> 00:37:06.930
very different especially from the neck
down, weren't really different in

00:37:06.930 --> 00:37:11.320
locomotor capabilities. If I had more
reconstructions of different Homo species

00:37:11.320 --> 00:37:15.160
you might have seen them look a little bit
different from one another. But basically,

00:37:15.160 --> 00:37:20.700
the picture is that there's not a dramatic
change here in the origin of Homo that has

00:37:20.700 --> 00:37:24.840
anything to do with the post cranial
skeleton. Perhaps the adaptive changes

00:37:24.840 --> 00:37:29.510
associated with the origin of the genus
had to do more with diet, other behaviors

00:37:29.510 --> 00:37:34.090
or something else. And that's what we need
to be thinking that what happened to the

00:37:34.090 --> 00:37:37.140
origin of Homo to give rise to all the
other great things that we've been hearing

00:37:37.140 --> 00:37:39.960
about today. I say thank you.

